HTTP Protocol
=============

+ General Protocol of transforming information through the Web.
+ HTTP message usually contains a JSON File.
+ HTTP Parts (URL Parts) :

          1. Scheme : http://
          2. Internet Address or Base URL : www.ibm.com
          3. Route : Location on the Web Server : /images/IDSNlogo.png
          
          
Request and Response
====================

Request Message :  
          
            + Request Start Line
            + Request Header
            + Request Body
            
Response Message :

            + Response Start Line
            + Response Header
            + Response Body (HTML Page)
            
Status Codes
============

1XX     -   Informational
100     -   Everything is OK so far.

2XX     -   Success
200     -   OK

3XX     -   Redirection
300     -   Multiple Choices

4XX     -   Client Error
401     -   Unauthorized
403     -   Forbidden
404     -   Not Found

500     -   Server Error
501     -   No Implemented.

HTTP Methods
============

GET       :-------  Retrieves Data from the Server.
POST      :-------  Submits Data to Server.
PUT       :-------  Updates Data already on Server.
DELETE    :-------  Delete Data from Server.
